Between the two camps.
MARK ANTONY
Their preparation is to-day by sea;We please them not by land.
SCARUS
For both, my lord.
MARK ANTONY
I would they'ld fight i' the fire or i' the air;We'ld fight there too.
But this it is; our footUpon the hills adjoining to the cityShall stay with us: order for sea is given;They have put forth the havenWhere their appointment we may best discover,And look on their endeavour.
